    "crit": 16,
    "description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Synthetic blood packs are shelf stable, sterile universal blood packs that are created in a lab, and used to aid in recovery. When using the Long Term Care action from the Treat Injury skill, a blood pack grants an additional 15 HP per day in healing. When using the Restore Hit Points action from the Treat Injury Skill, a blood pack grants an additional 3d4 HP of healing. When using the Surgery action from the Treat Injury skill, a blood pack reduces the time to recovery from fatigue, and the time required to complete a surgery, by half. A blood pack contains 4 units of synthetic blood. A character must have blood to benefit from synthetic blood packs.</span> <br style=\" font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; line-height: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: -webkit-auto; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; \"></p>"
